The paper discusses the development of an architecture for selecting parallel search strategies for optimal performance on a variety of search problems. This involves the use of machine learning techniques to select the optimal parallel search strategy for a given problem space. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses parallel and distributed approaches to search, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of machine learning techniques also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the testing of the system on different workstations, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper discusses planning problems, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.PL (Programming Languages).
